# ============================================================================
# Production Deployment Instructions
# ============================================================================
# 
# 1. Deploy Backend First:
#    - Use Railway, Render, Vercel, or Heroku
#    - Get the backend URL from the hosting dashboard
#    - Note: backend must be deployed BEFORE frontend
#
# 2. Set VITE_BACKEND_URL:
#    Replace 'your-backend-domain.com' with your actual backend URL
#    Result should look like:
#      VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://etherx-backend.railway.app
#
# 3. Update Vercel Environment Variables:
#    - Go to https://vercel.com → Your Project
#    - Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Add all variables from this file for 'Production' environment
#
# 4. Trigger Redeploy:
#    - Go to Deployments tab
#    - Click Redeploy on the latest deployment
#    - This will rebuild with new environment variables
#
# 5. Test:
#    - Open https://etherxsuite.vercel.app
#    - Open browser DevTools (F12) → Console
#    - Create a new sheet and try to save
#    - Look for "✅ Document uploaded to IPFS:" in logs
#    - If you see CORS errors, check backend FRONTEND_URL setting

# ============================================================================
# Important Notes
# ============================================================================
# 
# WebSocket URL:
#   - HTTPS frontend: Must use wss:// (secure WebSocket)
#   - HTTP frontend: Can use ws:// (regular WebSocket)
#   - Match the protocol: https + wss, http + ws
#
# CORS Configuration:
#   - Backend must have FRONTEND_URL set to your Vercel domain
#   - Or set CORS_ALLOW_ALL=true for preview deployments
#   - See backend .env.production.example for details
#
# Testing CORS:
#   - If document save fails with CORS error, check:
#     1. Browser console (F12) for the blocked origin
#     2. Backend logs for CORS rejection messages
#     3. Backend environment variables are set correctly
#     4. Frontend URL matches exactly (including https/http)
#
# Security:
#   - Never commit this file with real secrets
#   - Use Vercel Environment Variables dashboard
#   - Rotate JWT secrets regularly in backend
#   - Use strong database passwords
